Unit testing 

why?

Software can have bugs and the unit testing catches the bugs before they get to the field
Pour cela, on a besoin de plusieurs couches de test afin de repérer les éventuels bugs : 

Le niveau le plus bas - Unit testing : Testing at the function level.
- Component Testing : Testing is at the library and compiled binary level testing external interfaces of these components
- System Testing : Test the external interfaces of a system which is a collection of sub-systems
- Performance Testing : Testing done at sub-system and system levels to verify timing and resource usages are acceptable

Unit test testing individual functions in the code 
Each test case for the function should have a corresponding unit test
Groups of unit test can be combined into test suites, which can help with organizing the tests
Execution of the tests should be automated 

Un test unitaire comporte trois étapes :
- L'étape de configuration, où il crée la chaîne de test (Setup)
- L'étape d'action, où elle appelle le code de production pour effectuer l'action qui est testée  (Action)
- L'étape d'affirmation, où le test valide les résultats de l'action (Assertion)